name: $resourceType
desc: Returns the FHIR type name for this instance

desc: Returns: Identifier for this instance of the anatomical structure.

desc: Identifier for this instance of the anatomical structure.

name: $active
desc: Returns: Whether this body site is in active use.

name: $morphology
desc: Returns: The kind of structure being represented by the body structure at `BodyStructure.location`.  This can define both normal and abnormal morphologies.

pvardefs.desc: The kind of structure being represented by the body structure at `BodyStructure.location`.  This can define both normal and abnormal morphologies.

pvardefs.desc: The anatomical location or region of the specimen, lesion, or body structure.

desc: Returns: Qualifier to refine the anatomical location.  These include qualifiers for laterality, relative location, directionality, number, and plane.

desc: Qualifier to refine the anatomical location.  These include qualifiers for laterality, relative location, directionality, number, and plane.

name: $description
desc: Returns: A summary, characterization or explanation of the body structure.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: A summary, characterization or explanation of the body structure.

desc: Image or images used to identify a location.
